---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/page/PageHero.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Pattern Policy | Virtual Ventures"
  description="Clear usage rules for Virtual Ventures free crochet patterns, PDFs, finished items, QR codes and updates."
  showFooterBreadcrumbs={false}
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Pattern Rules"
    title="Pattern Policy"
    description="Friendly but firm rules for free website patterns, optional PDFs, finished item selling, safety notes and official updates."
  />

  <main class="page-shell">
    <section class="page-intro">
      <p class="eyebrow">Pattern policy</p>
      <h1>The making rules</h1>
      <p>
        This is the plain English home for how Virtual Ventures crochet patterns
        may be used, shared and checked.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Free patterns</h2>
        <p>
          Website patterns are free to read and use on the Virtual Ventures
          website. Free patterns may also have optional paid printable PDFs on
          Etsy and future printed yearly collections on KDP.
        </p>
        <p>
          Free does not mean public domain. The pattern wording, photos, notes,
          layout and files remain copyrighted.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>You may</h2>
        <p>
          You may make the project for yourself, make gifts, save the official
          website page for personal use, and share the original Virtual Ventures
          link with others.
        </p>
        <p>
          Unless a pattern says otherwise, you may sell small numbers of finished
          handmade items that you personally made from the pattern. A credit such
          as "Pattern by Virtual Ventures" is appreciated.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>You may not</h2>
        <p>
          You may not copy, repost, upload, resell, translate, redistribute,
          bundle or turn the pattern text, photos, charts, PDFs or files into
          your own download, course, kit, video, database or marketplace listing.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may not use Virtual Ventures product photos to sell your own
          finished items. Please photograph your own work so customers see what
          they are really buying.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Finished item selling</h2>
        <p>
          Small-scale finished item selling means handmade pieces made by you,
          in modest numbers, not factory production, mass outsourcing or print on
          demand-style pattern copying.
        </p>
        <p>
          You are responsible for your own materials, labels, safety checks,
          local rules, customer information, photos, pricing and shop policies.
          Please do not imply that Virtual Ventures made or tested your finished
          item.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Toy and safety notes</h2>
        <p>
          Crochet projects can include small parts such as safety eyes, buttons,
          stitch markers, beads, stuffing, wires, long cords or loose fibres.
          These may be choking or injury hazards for babies, children and pets.
        </p>
        <p>
          Unless a pattern or product clearly says otherwise, Virtual Ventures
          patterns are craft instructions, not a guarantee that a finished item
          is suitable as a tested toy.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Updates and versions</h2>
        <p>
          Patterns may be corrected, improved or clarified over time. Official
          updates, version numbers, correction notes and verification details
          should live on the Virtual Ventures website.
        </p>
        <p>
          QR codes may link to stitch help, livestream replays, pattern updates,
          copyright notes, policy pages and official verification pages.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-closing-card">
      <p>
        Make the thing, share the link, keep the pattern traceable. That is the
        tiny spellbook rule.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
